=render partial: "header"
=render partial: "menu2"
- @photo="adverts/"+@advert.id.to_s+".jpg"
.container.putcolor
  .col-sm-12
    .col-xs-12.padding20
      %h2.title_detail
        =@advert.title
  .col-sm-12
    .col-xs-4
      =image_tag( @photo )
    .col-xs-5
      %h1 Fixed Width Layout
      %p.lead The Bootstrap 3 grid is fluid only. This example shows how to use a custom container to create a fixed width layout.
      %p
      %a.btn.btn-large.btn-success{:href => "http://bootply.com/tagged/bootstrap-3", :target => "ext"} More Examples
    .col-xs-3.putcolor_prices
      .row.col-sm-12
        .col-xs-6
          1
        .col-xs-6
          2
      .row.col-sm-12
        .col-xs-12
          3
      .row.col-sm-12
        .col-xs-6
          4
        .col-xs-6
          5
  .row
    .col-lg-6
      %h4 Mobile First
      %p Responsive by default, and a clean "flat" design.
      %h4 Powerful Grid
      %p 3 responsive grid sizes to control the grid layout on tiny, small and large displays.
    .col-lg-6
      %h4 New Elements
      %p New panels, list groups, glyphicons and justified navigation.
      %h4 Less Bloat
      %p The optimized CSS is in a single file. Glyphicons are now separate.
  %hr
    .jumbotron.text-center
      %h2 Moving from Bootstrap 2.x to 3.0?
      %p.lead Everything has changed, so you can't just replace the 2.x with the 3.0 files. The folks at Bootply, the Bootstrap Playground have created a migration guide to help.
      %p
        %a.btn.btn-large.btn-success{:href => "http://www.bootply.com/bootstrap-3-migration-guide", :target => "ext"} Migration Guide